      article
        .inner
          p As a proprietary software solution built to manage millions of dollars in incoming and outgoing transactions, RECON has to be accurate. As a software system which employees spend hours a day looking at, RECON has to be good looking and easy to use.
          p My job is the second bit.
          h3 Lots and lots (and lots and lots) of data.
          img.shot(src="img/case-studies/recon/demographics-report.jpg")
          p Occasionally it is a struggle of design to codify a layout sensibility for pages which have very little relevent content. That is emphatically 
            i not 
            | the case here. The system pulls from massive databases worth of information in order to find the specific datapoints that are important to a specific user at a specific time.
          p This means coming up with a persistent language which the user can understand screen to screen, allowing them to do their job with more confidence.
          h3 Think, then rethink.
          img.shot(src="img/case-studies/recon/create-project.jpg")
          p The project has undergone a number of revisions based on focus groups, client meetings, and planning sessions. The concept of "edge cases" was dismissed as a concept we didn't believe in.
          p If the client felt a particular workflow was important to their business, we worked on a way to make that workflow happen.
          p Features and utilities were not simply bolted on. New features had to be considered holistically, and changes are made elsewhere to facilitate that change.
          img.shot(src="img/case-studies/recon/segmentation.jpg")
          h3 Learning the process to improve it.
          p A large education in building RECON was understanding how the clients want it to work. Having no experience in casino database marketing, I didn't understand what the parameters were of what users would like to do, or how I could help them do it.
          p Throughout the lifecycle of the project, I've had to become very familiar with their jobs, and then take every possible step to make that job better.
          p I'm sure that the screenshots you seeing could be confusing, but I've had enough communication with its intended users to know that it's the best of its kind for any software of its type, and that's something I have pride in.
          br
          h3 A few more looks...
          .last-looks
            img(src="img/case-studies/recon/signin.jpg")
            img(src="img/case-studies/recon/view-project.jpg")
            img(src="img/case-studies/recon/edit-tags.jpg")
